properties.Name: BenefitComponent
properties.Description:
The means by which the amount and type of benefits provided by the group life plan to members is determined.

Most employers will establish benefit schedules according to earnings, employment position or flat benefit.

Ex:
- Earnings
- Employment Position
- Flat Benefit

EARNINGS
The amount of life insurance provided to employees is based on their salary or earnings.

EMPLOYMENT POSITION
An employment position schedule sets the amount of life insurance to the employee's position with the company.

FLAT BENEFIT
A flat benefit schedule provides the same amount of life insurance to all employees regardless of earnings or position.
